                  </persName>
            . I went with the prosecutor and the prisoner Linsey. I heard him say he had taken four shillings of his master's money and gave it to the other prisoner, and that he had but two-pence halfpenny out of it.</p>
               <p>Linsey's Defence.</p>
               <p>I did not own to the breaking the lock neither the times before not that neither; the door was open. I do not believe it was locked.</p>
